=                The For Product Business Model

== Statement of Intent
Insure the production of essential goods and services.

== Terms of Operation
Pay with money to prepay for Future ProductsðŸŽ«.
Sign Work AgreementsðŸ“ƒ to prepay for Future Products.
Complete Work AgreementsðŸ“ƒ to gain land ownership.
Implicitly swap work when you pay for Future Products.
Land ownership is collateral to cover further risk.

== Legal Instruments
Crowdfunding: Each Product TicketðŸŽ« is an expiring claim of ownership over the future production of a specific good or service at some projected quantity and quality.
Private Property: Each Source Titleâ–¦ represent fractal ownership in land, tools, water-rights, mineral-rights, etc. required for production.
Labor Contracts: Each Work AgreementðŸ“ƒ represents a contract to achieve future production of a specific good or service at some projected quantity and quality.

== Code [Rules / Terms of Operation {Business Model, DAO}]
Sell Future Products for the money to buy Land without debt.
Land ownership vests to those who complete that production.
That land is held to avoid paying profit, rent and interest. (Own-to-Use)

== User Interface (UI)
